```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Protect Your SSN</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            padding: 20px;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: auto;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 5px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        h1 {
            text-align: center;
            color: #333;
        }
        label {
            display: block;
            margin-top: 10px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        input[type="text"], input[type="password"] {
            width: calc(100% - 22px);
            padding: 10px;
            margin-top: 5px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }
        button {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 10px;
            margin-top: 20px;
            background-color: #007BFF;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 4px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #0056b3;
        }
        .error-message {
            color: red;
            font-size: 0.9em;
            margin-top: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Protect Your Social Security Number (SSN)</h1>

<form id="ssnForm">
    <label for="ssn">Enter Your Social Security Number (SSN):</label>
    <input type="text" id="ssn" name="ssn" placeholder="####-##-####" pattern="\d{3}-\d{2}-\d{4}" required>
    <span class="error-message" id="ssnError"></span>

    <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>

<script>
    document.getElementById('ssnForm').addEventListener('submit', function(event) {
        event.preventDefault();

        const ssn = document.getElementById('ssn').value;
        const ssnPattern = /\d{3}-\d{2}-\d{4}/;

        if (!ssn.match(ssnPattern)) {
            document.getElementById('ssnError').textContent = 'Please enter a valid SSN in the format ####-##-####.';
        } else {
            document.getElementById('ssnError').textContent = '';
            // Here you can add code to handle the submission, e.g., sending the SSN to a server
            alert('SSN submitted successfully!');
        }
    });
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
1. **HTML Structure**:
   - The form includes a label for the SSN input field.
   - An input field for the SSN with a specific pattern to ensure it is in the correct format.
   - A button to submit the form.
   - A span element to display error messages.

2. **CSS Styling**:
   - Basic styling to make the form look clean and user-friendly.
   - Centering the form and adding some padding and margins.

3. **JavaScript Validation**:
   - The form uses JavaScript to validate the SSN format before submission.
   - If the SSN is not in the correct format, an error message is displayed.
   - If the SSN is valid, a success message is shown (you can replace this with actual form submission logic).

This form ensures that users understand the importance of entering their SSN correctly and provides immediate feedback if the input is invalid.

